<div type="a">
<column>1</column>
<head>Altered Greenbacks</head>
<origin></origin>
<commentary></commentary>
<transcript></transcript>
<trailer></trailer>
<names></names>
<summary>Counterfeiters are beginning to alter two-dollar greenbacks into fifties. When
compared, the difference is obvious. While the bills have the same engraving in the center, the
head is between the words "United" and "States" on the fifties, whereas on the twos the words are
above the engraving. The genuine fifty dollar notes are covered on the back with the number 50.
One person has been caught using them, and those people who deal in fifties are warned to be on
the look out.</summary>
<note></note>
<look></look>
</div>

